The paper discusses a clustering method for large-scale data analysis, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), and data science (cs.DS). The method involves compressing input vectors into product-quantized codes, which is a technique used in database systems (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
